<div class="onboarding-header">
  <IconTile @icon="download" />
  <div class="onboarding-header-content">
    <h1>Install the Derrick CLI</h1>
    <p>First, you'll need to install the Derrick CLI via Homebrew or a manual installation.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="onboarding-step">
  <p>Anyone using Derrick to deploy from their workstation needs to install it locally. The below
    instructions guide you through that for various operating systems.
  </p>
  <p>If you need to compile Derrick from source instead, see the <ExternalLink href="https://derrick.dev/docs">documentation</ExternalLink>.</p>

  <h2>Install Derrick</h2>

  <Pds::TabNav>
    <LinkTo @route="onboarding.install.manual">Manual installation</LinkTo>
    <LinkTo @route="onboarding.install.homebrew">Homebrew on OS X</LinkTo>
    <LinkTo @route="onboarding.install.chocolatey">Chocolatey on Windows</LinkTo>
    <LinkTo @route="onboarding.install.linux">Linux</LinkTo>
  </Pds::TabNav>

  {{outlet}}

  <h2>Verify the installation</h2>

  <p>After installing Derrick, verify that the installation worked by opening a new terminal session and running the
    command <code>derrick</code>.</p>

  <CopyableCode @ref="verify-derrick">
    <pre><code id="verify-derrick">derrick</code></pre>
  </CopyableCode>

  <pre><code class="output">usage: derrick [-version] [-help] [-autocomplete-(un)install] &lt;command&gt; [&lt;args&gt;]

Common commands:
    build        Build a new versioned artifact from source.
    deploy       Deploy a pushed artifact.
  ...</code></pre>

  <p>If you get an error that <code>derrick</code> could not be found, your <code>PATH</code> environment variable was
    not set up properly. Make sure that your <code>PATH</code> variable contains the directory where you installed
    Derrick.</p>
</div>

<hr />

